        "title": "Fix Linux OpenCode Go and Command Code usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- enable OpenCode Go local SQLite usage on Linux through a system SQLite module\n- allow Command Code billing on Linux when a manual cookie is configured\n- carry Command Code cookie settings into CLI snapshots and document Linux source behavior\n- add Linux SQLite, source-gating, settings, and strategy regressions\n\nFixes #1657.\n\n## Proof\nExact head: `5056c542a03c5f0e34970afb383ecb9efdd47ad8`\n\n- `swift test --filter 'CLIEntryTests|TokenAccountEnvironmentPrecedenceTests|CommandCodeProviderTests|OpenCodeGoProviderStrategyTests|OpenCodeGoLinuxTests'` (62 passed)\n- `swift test --filter CommandCodeUsageFetcherTests` (20 passed)\n- `make check`\n- `make docs-list`\n- autoreview: clean, 0.83\n- Crabbox Linux / Swift 6.2.1 release build on code-identical pre-rebase head `89522516`: OpenCode Go read a real SQLite fixture and returned `source: local`; Command Code with a configured invalid cookie reached the live API and returned invalid-session rather than macOS/browser gating. The final rebase only incorporates landed #1648.\n\nA local aggregate `swift test` run executed 4,440 tests and hit 12 timing-only failures in existing process/deadline/WebKit suites. Changed-area and isolated affected suites pass; hosted sharded CI is the merge gate.\n",
